dct_description_sm: From surveys by the Chinese Maritime Customs between 1916 and 1930 ; published May, 1916, at the Hydrographic Office, under the authority of the Secretary of the Navy.
Depths shown by soundings, tints, and isolines; relief by contours and spot heights.
Tidal information and "average direction and rate of tidal streams" tables, buoy legend, navigational notes.
Shows low water areas, islands, drainage, lights, vegetation/wetlands, roads, railroads, telegraph cables.
Various points of interest, such as "chapel," "wreck," "submerged masonry."
